mission_executor  | 
mission_executor  | **The problem:** To get GREEN, I would have to omit the abdominal CT. For a young adult with severe abdominal pain + fever + nausea, imaging (CT, or ultrasound as an alternative) is the standard of care to evaluate for appendicitis and other surgical abdomens. Labs alone cannot rule out appendicitis — a normal WBC does not exclude it, and relying on labs alone risks a missed surgical emergency.
mission_executor  | 
